    • Class com.analog.lyric.dimple.factorfunctions.core.SparseFactorTableBase extends FactorTableBase implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • _representation

          int _representation
          Bit mask indicating how the contents of the table are represented. Exposed by SparseFactorTableBase.getRepresentation() and SparseFactorTableBase.setRepresentation(FactorTableRepresentation).

          This is a combination of the bits:

          • FactorTable.DENSE_ENERGY,
          • FactorTable.DENSE_WEIGHT,
          • FactorTable.SPARSE_ENERGY,
          • FactorTable.SPARSE_WEIGHT
          • FactorTable.SPARSE_INDICES.

        • _sparseEnergies

          double[] _sparseEnergies

        • _sparseWeights

          double[] _sparseWeights

        • _nonZeroWeights

          int _nonZeroWeights
          Count of table entries with non-zero weight/non-infinite energy.

          When table has no sparse representation, this is returned as the IFactorTableBase.sparseSize().

        • _sparseIndices

          int[][] _sparseIndices
          Same information as FactorTable's _sparseIndexToJointIndex but instead of storing joint indices stores arrays of element indices.

        • _computedMask

          int _computedMask
          Information computed about the table based on its values. This field is zeroed out whenever table weights or energies are changed.

          Consists of the bitsL

          • FactorTable.DETERMINISTIC_COMPUTED
          • SparseFactorTableBase.NORMALIZED
          • SparseFactorTableBase.NORMALIZED_COMPUTED
          • SparseFactorTableBase.CONDITIONAL
          • SparseFactorTableBase.CONDITIONAL_COMPUTED.
